The concept is this: a char is encoded as a byte, which is a number. Check out a related [ASCII table][1] where you can see that &#39;a&#39; has the value 97 (decimal), &#39;b&#39; has 98... So if we subtract 97 from all our chars we can reach the desired values. 

&lt;pre&gt;

    char   byte(decimal)   char value -97
    a        97                  0
    b        98                  1
    ...      ...                ...
    z        122                 24
&lt;/pre&gt;


